cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR, cs.NE 

This paper is about aspect-based sentiment analysis using deep learning techniques, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also proposes a new neural network architecture with attention mechanism, which involves training and optimizing the model, making it relevant to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves analyzing and processing textual data, which is related to information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses LSTMs and attention mechanisms, which are common techniques in neural networks and deep learning, making it relevant to the neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
